  "canonical_definition": "EGGF (Entity Gravity Graph Framework) is a portable publishing-and-credibility architecture that organizes intellectual work around a central Entity exhibiting gravity, where every authored Body has one canonical URL, every Pathway between Bodies is typed, and the resulting graph is exposed at a manifest endpoint so AI assistants and search systems can traverse a creator's authorship as infrastructure rather than reconstructing it from scattered HTML.",
